DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">The City of Bloomington invites nonprofit organiza
 tions to apply for funding through the <a href="https://bloomington.in.gov/
 digital-equity-grants"><b><u>Digital Opportunity Grants program</u></b></a>
  to support their efforts to bridge the digital divide and increase digital
  resources for residents. Digital opportunity refers to the fair distributi
 on of the internet and modern technology throughout society. </p><p dir="lt
 r">Bloomington-based nonprofits may apply from Monday\, June 16\, to 5 p.m.
  on Wednesday\, July 16 to receive up to $55\,000 in grant funding. Proposa
 ls will be accepted online at <a href="http://bloomington.in.gov/digital-op
 portunity"><b><u>bloomington.in.gov/digital-opportunity</u></b></a>.</p><br
 ><a href="https://bloomington.in.gov/digital-opportunity-grants" target="_b
 lank">https://bloomington.in.gov/digital-opportunity-grants</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250904T151046Z
LOCATION:https://bloomington.in.gov/digital-opportunity-grants
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Bloomington Digital Opportunity Grants Application Period Opens
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
