DESCRIPTION:Let’s talk about Indiana Senate Bill 1 (SB1) and what it could 
 mean for Bloomington—join us Wednesday\, April 23 from 10-11 a.m. at the Mo
 nroe Convention Center (302 S College Ave).<br><br>The recent passage of SB
 1 at the Statehouse—and the arrival of this year’s property tax bills—has r
 aised important questions about how this legislation will affect local comm
 unities.<br><br>While originally positioned as a way to provide tax relief\
 , new changes to SB1 have left many wondering what it means for cities like
  Bloomington\, as well as for schools\, counties\, and residents across Ind
 iana. Join Mayor Kerry Thomson and a panel of local leaders for a nonpartis
 an\, educational discussion focused on the local impact of SB1 and how we c
 an work together to support the long-term needs of our region. Panelist inc
 lude:<br><br><ul><li>City of Bloomington Mayor Kerry Thomson</li><li>Eric R
 eedy and Tim Stricker\, Reedy Financial Group</li><li>Jen Pearl\, Bloomingt
 on Economic Development Corporation</li><li>Hopi Stosberg\, Bloomington Cit
 y Council President</li><li>Talisha Coppock\, Downtown Bloomington\, Inc.</
 li><li>Eric Spoonmore\, Greater Bloomington Chamber of Commerce</li><li>Jod
 y Madeira\, Monroe County Commissioner<br><br></li></ul>This event is open 
 to the public and press. All are welcome.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250820T203436Z
LOCATION:Monroe Convention Center\, 302 S College Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47
 403\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Understanding SB1: A Community Conversation
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
