DESCRIPTION:<br>Don’t miss the next Traveling Town Hall with Mayor Kerry Th
 omson! Join us on Tuesday\, December 3\, from 6 to 7:30 p.m. at Monroe Publ
 ic Library — Downtown\, located at 303 E. Kirkwood Avenue. Council member S
 ydney Zulich will also be in attendance.<br><br>As part of our commitment t
 o accessible government\, Traveling Town Halls provide an opportunity for r
 esidents to engage directly with local officials\, ask questions\, and lear
 n more about city projects and services. Held every other month by district
 \, these events bring government closer to you—all are welcome!<br><br>Here
 ’s what you can expect:<br><br>• Upon arrival\, you’ll receive an index car
 d to jot down any questions or comments you have for Mayor Thomson and the 
 council. Whether it’s about city projects or just a good idea you’ve been h
 olding onto\, we encourage you to anonymously share your thoughts.<br><br>•
  At 6 p.m\, Mayor Thomson will kick things off with a brief update on the l
 atest city projects and initiatives.<br><br>• Mayor Thomson and Council wil
 l then read through the collected index cards\, addressing the questions yo
 u’ve asked.<br><br>• If time allows\, we’ll wrap up with a live Q&amp\;A se
 ssion to address any additional questions you may have.<br><br>For more inf
 ormation\, please contact the Office of the Mayor at 812-349-3406 or visit 
 the City of Bloomington’s website at<a href="http://www.bloomington.in.gov/
 "><u> bloomington.in.gov</u></a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250820T203430Z
LOCATION:Monroe County Public Library - Downtown\, 303 E Kirkwood Ave\, Blo
 omington\, IN 47408\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mayor Kerry Thomson's Traveling Town Hall
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
