ORGANIZER;CN=c_8646f71c727ce228818cbf044b85d69a4a9e28ceff939d6525d22224ceb7
 9551@group.calendar.google.com:mailto:c_8646f71c727ce228818cbf044b85d69a4a9
 e28ceff939d6525d22224ceb79551@group.calendar.google.com
UID:3djkui73qr2cha6v1kidcbq842@google.com
ATTENDEE;CUTYPE=INDIVIDUAL;ROLE=REQ-PARTICIPANT;PARTSTAT=ACCEPTED;CN=Depart
 ment Events;X-NUM-GUESTS=0:mailto:bloomington.in.gov_c657mi332p5sjpq2lcht9i
 mu60@group.calendar.google.com
CREATED:20250108T152013Z
DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">The City of Bloomington invites residents to a pub
 lic meeting on Tuesday\, January 7 from 5:30 to 6:30 p.m. at the Bloomingto
 n Police Department\, 220 E. 3rd Street\, to discuss considerations for the
  future location of the Bloomington Police Department (BPD) headquarters.</
 p><p dir="ltr">The session will begin with Mayor Kerry Thomson's introducti
 on and background presentation\, providing an overview of the factors and g
 uiding principles shaping the City’s exploration of potential sites. Chris 
 Ciolli\, Project Executive with Weddle Bros. Construction Companies\, will 
 follow up with a discussion on possible opportunities for the project.</p><
 p dir="ltr">Additionally\, the meeting will include an update on the status
  of the public safety bond\, which will help fund improvements aimed at enh
 ancing safety and operational efficiency for BPD and the community it serve
 s.<br><br>The meeting will be broadcast live on Community Access Television
  Services (CATS) and available for on-demand viewing afterward at <a href="
 http://catstv.net"><u>catstv.net</u></a>.</p>For more information\, please 
 contact the Office of the Mayor at 812-349-3406 or <a href="mailto:comms@bl
 oomington.in.gov"><u>comms@bloomington.in.gov</u></a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250820T203433Z
LOCATION:Bloomington Police Department\, 220 E 3rd St\, Bloomington\, IN 47
 401\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Public Meeting on Future Police Headquarters
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
