DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">Out of an abundance of caution due to the anticipa
 ted winter storm\, the Traveling Town Hall scheduled for Monday\, January 2
 6\, will now be <a href="https://bloomington.zoom.us/j/87487866209?pwd=r5Lx
 4YtaKf7R5JbbvZfYVDUj4OYTNo.1"><b><u>held virtually via Zoom</u></b></a>. Ma
 yor Kerry Thomson\, Katherine Zaiger\, Director of City of Bloomington Util
 ities\, and Councilmember Isabel Piedmont-Smith will host the online event 
 on Monday\, January 26\, from 6 to 7 p.m.</p><p dir="ltr">Traveling Town Ha
 lls are designed to give residents the opportunity to connect directly with
  local leaders\, ask questions\, and learn more about City projects and ini
 tiatives. The evening will begin with a brief update from Mayor Thomson\, f
 ollowed by a discussion focused on city initiatives and neighborhood priori
 ties.</p><p dir="ltr">Participants will be able to submit questions during 
 the virtual session\, which City leadership will address as time allows.</p
 ><p dir="ltr">The event is free and open to the public. Community members m
 ay <a href="https://bloomington.zoom.us/j/87487866209?pwd=r5Lx4YtaKf7R5Jbbv
 ZfYVDUj4OYTNo.1"><b><u>join virtually using the Zoom</u></b></a> informatio
 n below:</p><p dir="ltr"><a href="https://bloomington.zoom.us/j/87487866209
 ?pwd=r5Lx4YtaKf7R5JbbvZfYVDUj4OYTNo.1"><u>https://bloomington.zoom.us/j/874
 87866209?pwd=r5Lx4YtaKf7R5JbbvZfYVDUj4OYTNo.1</u></a> </p><p dir="ltr">Meet
 ing ID: 874 8786 6209</p><p dir="ltr">Passcode: 198390</p><p dir="ltr">—</p
 ><p dir="ltr">One tap mobile</p><p dir="ltr">+13052241968\,\,87487866209#\,
 \,\,\,*198390# US</p><p dir="ltr"><br></p><p dir="ltr">For more information
 \, please contact Desiree DeMolina\, Communications Director\, Office of th
 e Mayor at <a href="mailto:desiree.demolina@bloomington.in.gov"><u>desiree.
 demolina@bloomington.in.gov</u></a>.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260124T190538Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Virtual Traveling Town Hall
TRANSP:OPAQUE
