DESCRIPTION:<br>Join Mayor Kerry Thomson and Margie Rice\, Corporation Coun
 sel for the City of Bloomington\, for an open discussion about annexation a
 nd its impact on our community. This session will provide an update on the 
 annexation process and offer residents an opportunity to share their though
 ts\, ask questions\, and learn more about the city’s role and responsibilit
 ies in annexation.<br><br>The discussion will also highlight the role of an
 nexation and regional governance in fostering equitable\, sustainable\, and
  economically strong metropolitan areas.<br><br>When: Monday\, December 9\,
  2024\, from 5:30 to 6:30 p.m.<br>Where: Monroe County Public Library—South
 west Branch // 890 W Gordon Pike<br><br>Mayor Thomson acknowledges that the
  annexation process has not always been handled well in the past and is com
 mitted to fostering transparency\, listening to residents\, and ensuring ev
 ery voice is heard and valued as we work together to shape Bloomington’s fu
 ture.<br>This event is free and open to the public. We look forward to seei
 ng you there!<br><br>For more information\, please contact the Office of th
 e Mayor at 812-349-3406 or visit the City of Bloomington’s website at<a hre
 f="http://www.bloomington.in.gov/"><u> bloomington.in.gov</u></a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250820T203431Z
LOCATION:Monroe County Public Library - Southwest Branch\, 890 W Gordon Pik
 e\, Bloomington\, IN 47403\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Annexation Listening Session
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
