DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">The City of Bloomington invites nonprofit organiza
 tions to apply for funding through the <a href="https://www.google.com/url?
 q=https://bloomington.in.gov/digital-equity-grants&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=ca
 lendar&amp\;ust=1756667459587542&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2MeRaPD4npfiWiBWIM3UEK" tar
 get="_blank"><b><u>Digital Opportunity Grants program</u></b></a> to suppor
 t their efforts to bridge the digital divide and increase digital resources
  for residents. Digital opportunity refers to the fair distribution of the 
 internet and modern technology throughout society. </p><p dir="ltr">Bloomin
 gton-based nonprofits may apply from Monday\, June 16\, to 5 p.m. on Wednes
 day\, July 16 to receive up to $55\,000 in grant funding. Proposals will be
  accepted online at <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://bloomingto
 n.in.gov/digital-opportunity&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=175666
 7459587542&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0GjpvMXR6AMAXVahAXPzpT" target="_blank"><b><u>blo
 omington.in.gov/digital-opportunity</u></b></a>.</p><br><a href="https://ww
 w.google.com/url?q=https://bloomington.in.gov/digital-opportunity-grants&am
 p\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1756667459587542&amp\;usg=AOvVaw24bdO
 Pa865EovPFZFTSxNe" target="_blank">https://bloomington.in.gov/digital-oppor
 tunity-grants</a>
