DESCRIPTION:Join Mayor Kerry Thomson\, City of Bloomington Utilities Direct
 or Katherine Zaiger\, and Corporation Counsel Margie Rice for the District 
 4 Traveling Town Hall on Monday\, August 4 from 6–7 p.m. at Morgenstern Boo
 ks &amp\; Café (849 S Auto Mall Road).<br><br>This event offers residents t
 he chance to connect directly with City leaders\, ask questions\, and learn
  more about key projects and city services—this month with a special focus 
 on drinking water\, stormwater\, and wastewater!<br><br>The evening will be
 gin with brief updates from the Mayor\, followed by a Q&amp\;A session base
 d on submitted questions. If time allows\, the event will conclude with liv
 e questions from attendees.<br><br>Traveling Town Halls are held in a diffe
 rent district every other month as part of the City’s commitment to transpa
 rent\, accessible government. Residents of District 4—and anyone interested
  in how city services are delivered—are encouraged to attend.<br><br>The me
 eting will be broadcast live on Community Access Television Services (CATS)
  and available for on-demand viewing at <b><a href="http://catstv.net/">cat
 stv.net</a></b>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250820T203440Z
LOCATION:Morgenstern Books & Café\, 849 S Auto Mall Rd\, Bloomington\, IN 4
 7401\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mayor Kerry Thomson's Traveling Town Hall
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
