DESCRIPTION:Mayor Kerry Thomson will deliver the 2025 State of the City Add
 ress on Thursday\, April 3 at the Waldron Arts Center (122 S Walnut St).\n\
 nThe event is free and open to the public\, with doors opening at 5:30 p.m.
  and the presentation beginning promptly at 6 p.m.\, followed by a receptio
 n with city leadership and community partners.\n\nThis annual address provi
 des residents with an update on Bloomington’s progress\, priorities\, and v
 ision for the future. Mayor Thomson will outline key initiatives related to
  housing\, economic development\, public safety\, infrastructure\, engageme
 nt\, and long-term financial strategies.\n\nThe evening will begin with a p
 resentation of the colors by the Bloomington Police and Fire Departments\, 
 followed by the National Anthem performed by Andrea de la Rosa\, Assistant 
 Director of Small Business Development. The program will conclude with a pe
 rformance by Girls Rock Bloomington.\n\nFor those unable to attend in perso
 n\, the event will be broadcast live and available for later viewing throug
 h Community Access Television Services (CATS) at catstv.net.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250820T203435Z
LOCATION:John Waldron Arts Center\, 122 S Walnut St\, Bloomington\, IN 4740
 4\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:2025 State of the City
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
