DTEND:20240318T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020722Z
ORGANIZER;CN=c_8646f71c727ce228818cbf044b85d69a4a9e28ceff939d6525d22224ceb7
 9551@group.calendar.google.com:mailto:c_8646f71c727ce228818cbf044b85d69a4a9
 e28ceff939d6525d22224ceb79551@group.calendar.google.com
UID:6u1obukofjnaqd0kfck5f85pfo@google.com
ATTENDEE;CUTYPE=INDIVIDUAL;ROLE=REQ-PARTICIPANT;PARTSTAT=ACCEPTED;CN=Depart
 ment Events;X-NUM-GUESTS=0:mailto:bloomington.in.gov_c657mi332p5sjpq2lcht9i
 mu60@group.calendar.google.com
CREATED:20240228T201303Z
DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">Mayor Kerry Thomson is committed to an open govern
 ment that is accessible to all Bloomington residents. In that spirit\, she 
 will be out in the community conducting a series of traveling town hall mee
 tings. Every other month\, a listening session will be held in each of the 
 <a href="https://bloomington.in.gov/arcgis/apps/webappviewer/index.html?id=
 eff5d0cce43c4f1ab7752d4d315ba3e2"><u>six City Council districts</u></a>\, s
 tarting in District 1\, represented by Councilmember Isabel Piedmont-Smith.
  In the intervening months\, Mayor Thomson will hold a town hall on a speci
 fic topical issue.</p><p dir="ltr"><br></p><p dir="ltr">The first listening
  session will take place on Monday\, March 18\, 6-7:30pm at Summit Elementa
 ry School\, 1450 W Countryside Ln. Mayor Thomson will be accompanied by Cou
 ncilmembers as well as Planning and Transportation and Housing and Neighbor
 hood Development department directors.</p><p dir="ltr"><br></p><p dir="ltr"
 >What questions or concerns do you have? What issues are important to you? 
 How can the City better serve the community? Please attend the town hall in
  your district\, or another one that fits your schedule\, for an opportunit
 y to engage directly with City officials. </p><p dir="ltr"><br></p><p dir="
 ltr">Details about future traveling town halls will be announced via the Ci
 ty’s social media channels\, so keep a lookout for a town hall near you. Th
 e tentative schedule is as follows:</p><p dir="ltr"><br></p><ul><li dir="lt
 r"><p dir="ltr">March\, Council District 1: listening session</p></li><li d
 ir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">April: topical issue</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="lt
 r">May\, Council District 2: listening session</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir
 ="ltr">June: topical issue</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">July\, Counci
 l District 3: listening session</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">August: 
 topical issue</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">September\, Council Distri
 ct 4: listening session</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">October: topical
  issue</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">November\, Council District 5: li
 stening session</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">December: topical issue<
 /p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">January\, Council District 6: listening 
 session</p></li></ul><p dir="ltr"><br></p><p dir="ltr">If you are unsure of
  your Council district\, <a href="https://bloomington.in.gov/mybloomington/
 "><u>visit myBloomington and enter your address</u></a>. Have suggestions a
 bout an issue you would like addressed in one of the upcoming topical issue
  meetings? Send an email to <a href="mailto:mayor@bloomington.in.gov"><u>ma
 yor@bloomington.in.gov</u></a>\, and include “town hall” in the subject lin
 e.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250820T203427Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:MAYOR THOMSON TO HOLD TRAVELING TOWN HALLS
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
