DESCRIPTION:<div class="page" title="Page 2"><div class="section"><div clas
 s="layoutArea"><div class="column"><p><span style="font-size: 12.000000pt\;
  font-family: 'AvenirNextLTPro'\; font-weight: 600">You’re invited </span><
 span style="font-size: 12.000000pt\; font-family: 'AvenirNextLTPro'">to a c
 ivic code and designchallenge focused on improving citizen issuereporting. 
 Bloomington’s citizen reportingtools – using the Open311 API – need a desig
 nand code refresh. That’s where you come in!&nbsp\; http://www.thecombine.o
 rg</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 12.000000pt\; font-family: 'AvenirN
 extLTPro'">The City of Bloomington’s Information and Technology Services De
 partment and Departmentof Innovation are seeking a web-basedapplication tha
 t allows citizens to easily reportissues in areas ranging from potholes top
 laygrounds\, from water to waste\, and more.The winning application may (wi
 th somemodification) be put into production use&nbsp\;</span><span style="f
 ont-family: AvenirNextLTPro\; font-size: 12pt\;">at the City of Bloomington
 .</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 12.000000pt\; font-family: 'AvenirNe
 xtLTPro'">A total of $1\,000 will be awarded courtesy ofthe City’s Innovati
 on Fund. Teams can be ofany size. The best part: you can get startedright n
 ow!</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250904T151028Z
LOCATION:Monroe County Convention Center
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Combine - Civic Code and Design Challenge
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
