DESCRIPTION:<br>Looking for an opportunity to connect with local leaders\, 
 ask questions\, and get the scoop on city projects? Mayor Kerry Thomson is 
 hosting a Traveling Town Hall on Monday\, April 7\, at Banneker Community C
 enter\, 930 W 7th Street\, from 6 to 7 p.m. Joining the Mayor will be Parks
  &amp\; Recreation Director\, Tim Street\, ready to share updates and answe
 r your burning questions. Here’s how it works:<br><br>• The evening kicks o
 ff with Mayor Thomson’s quick rundown of city initiatives.<br><br>• Submit 
 your questions on index cards (provided at the door)\, and the team will ta
 ckle as many as possible.<br><br>• If time allows\, a live Q&amp\;A will ro
 und out the night!<br><br>These Town Halls happen every other month in diff
 erent districts\, giving residents a chance to engage directly with City Ha
 ll. Whether you live in District 2 or just love being in the know about Blo
 omington’s happenings\, this is your chance to join the conversation.<br><b
 r>Can’t make it? The meeting will be broadcast live on Community Access Tel
 evision Services (CATS) and available on-demand at <a href="http://catstv.n
 et/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR3mRsDk9MuWCywqMFynvZn_EnfyopfKw0PYC2Jrb3dUfk
 XBNcqmPCUV_Ac_aem_SSUi2nchuFjm1KpJyfD3NQ" target="_blank">catstv.net.</a><b
 r><br>Mark your calendar\, bring your questions\, and let’s chat about the 
 projects shaping Bloomington!
LAST-MODIFIED:20250820T203435Z
LOCATION:City Of Bloomington Parks And Recreation - Food Distribution Cente
 r\, 930 W 7th St\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mayor Kerry Thomson's Traveling Town Hall
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
