DESCRIPTION:Join Mayor Kerry Thomson\, Director of Economic and Sustainable
  Development Jane Kupersmith\, and Councilmember Hopi Stosberg for the Dist
 rict 3 Traveling Town Hall. This event offers residents the chance to conne
 ct directly with City leaders\, ask questions\, and learn more about key pr
 ojects and city services.<br><br>The evening will begin with brief updates 
 from the Mayor\, followed by a Q&amp\;A session based on submitted question
 s. If time allows\, the event will conclude with live questions from attend
 ees.<br><br>Traveling Town Halls are held in a different district every oth
 er month as part of the City’s commitment to transparent\, accessible gover
 nment. Residents of District 3—and anyone interested in how city services a
 re delivered—are encouraged to attend.<br><br>The meeting will be broadcast
  live on Community Access Television Services (CATS) and available for on-d
 emand viewing at <b><a href="http://catstv.net">catstv.net</a></b>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250820T203437Z
LOCATION:University Elementary School\, 1111 N Russell Rd\, Bloomington\, I
 N 47408\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mayor Kerry Thomson's Traveling Town Hall
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
