CREATED:20251003T141905Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Mayor Kerry Thomson invites residents to the next
  Traveling Town Hall on Monday\, October 6\, from 6 to 7 p.m. at Jackson Cr
 eek Middle School (3980 S. Sare Road) in District 5.</b></strong> The event
  will feature Housing and Neighborhood Development (HAND) Director Anna Kil
 lion-Hanson and will have a special focus on housing.</p><p>Town Halls allo
 w residents to connect directly with local leaders\, ask questions\, and le
 arn more about city initiatives. The event will begin with a brief update f
 rom Mayor Thomson on current and upcoming projects. Following the update\, 
 attendees can submit questions on index cards distributed at the door\, whi
 ch the City leadership panel will address. If time permits\, the evening wi
 ll conclude with a live Q&amp\;A session for additional questions.</p><p>Re
 sidents of District 5 and community members citywide are encouraged to atte
 nd\, especially those with feedback or questions related to housing. The ev
 ent offers an opportunity to engage directly with City leadership and learn
  more about ongoing initiatives and operations.</p><p>The meeting will be b
 roadcast live on Community Access Television Services (CATS) and available 
 for on-demand viewing a <a href="http://catstv.net/"><u><strong><b>catstv.n
 et</b></strong></u></a>. </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251003T150717Z
LOCATION:3980 S. Sare Road
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mayor Kerry Thomson's Traveling Town Hall
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
